<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-329-080  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 329 080.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  May 11 1989 v15 n10 p18(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New GIS applications mean info consumption. (geographicinformation systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wintrob, Suzanne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Geographic information systems (GIS) have become standaloneproducts that can be tailored to the electronic mapping,modification, and analysis of data for scientific, business,defense, and intelligence applications.andP;  Such systems areexemplified by Tydac Technologies Inc's SPANS (Spatial AnalysisSystem), of which 300 have been sold worldwide.andP;  Severalapplications are briefly described: production of insectmanifestation based on rainfall, pesticide use, and soil type inAlberta; the United Nation's Global Resource Information Databaseproject, which is creating databases of land, climate andinfrastructure information; and a commercial project to assess thedemographics of Miracle Food Mart's customers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MapsGeographic Information SystemsApplicationsUtilizationTrendsMarket Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>